OL,5, A sculpture honouring Guglielmo Marconi
OL,6, could be abandoned after councillors   
OL,7, learned of his support for Mussolini.  
OL,9,FCardiff council had planned to erect   
OL,10,Fthe artwork to celebrate Marconi's feat
OL,11,Fof transmitting a radio signal across  
OL,12,Fopen sea off the Welsh coast in 1897.  
OL,14,FThe 4m (13ft) high sculpture of a radio
OL,15,Fis due to be part of a #1.1m project   
OL,16,Ffor the Cardiff Bay barrage area.      
OL,18,FHowever the plans are now under review 
OL,19,Fafter the council became aware of his  
OL,20,Fsupport of Italy's fascist government. 
